<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,335,912,938]" box="[189,335,912,938]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,912,938]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,912,938]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,887,959,1021]" box="[234,378,959,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,959,985]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Male</emphasis>
(n=1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,887,959,1021]" box="[189,887,994,1021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,359,995,1021]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[524,654,994,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[524,654,994,1020]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[662,752,995,1021]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[188,1401,1060,1438]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
Frons about 0.25 × head width at level of ocellar triangle; 10 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; first flagellomere approximately 4× as long as pedicel; thorax with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity (
<figureCitation box="[526,616,1130,1156]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[245,1342,265,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-12@7.[245,1342,265,1785]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Dexosarcophaga spp., male habitus and terminalia. A–B. Dexosarcophaga phoenix sp. nov., holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Terminalia, lateral view. C–D. Dexosarcophaga jandainae sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MZUSP [lost]), Brazil, Mato Grosso, Chapada dos Guimarães. C. Habitus, lateral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. E. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]), habitus, lateral view. F. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]), habitus, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823736" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823736/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); intra-alars 2 +2, postpronotals 2; meral setae 5–7; scutellum with pair of reduced apical setae; abdomen dark brown, with golden pollinosity; T5 with row of 12 marginal setae; cercus with pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[594,727,1201,1227]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6B–C</figureCitation>
); surstylus trapezium-shaped in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1383,1201,1227]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
); pregonite almost straight, 1.5× length of postgonite and with broad base (
<figureCitation box="[1076,1173,1236,1262]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); vesica consisting of membranous and sclerotized areas and with ventral dark lobe with 2–3 spines (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1319,1271,1297]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D–E</figureCitation>
); juxta equipped with numerous spines (
<figureCitation box="[570,697,1306,1332]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D–E</figureCitation>
); median stylus with enlarged base and narrow apex, slightly shorter than lateral stylus, base curved towards ventral and dorsal margins of paraphallus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[278,408,1377,1403]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D–E</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus with base slightly curved towards ventral margin of paraphallus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[417,545,1412,1438]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
