<paragraph blockId="12.[189,304,1690,1716]" box="[189,304,1690,1716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,1690,1716]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,1690,1716]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[188,1399,1736,2009]" lastBlockId="14.[188,1399,265,362]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,470,1736,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,470,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Dexosarcophaga limon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[482,578,1737,1763]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[955,1059,1737,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[955,1059,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1071,1166,1737,1763]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lopes, 1982)" baseAuthorityName="Lopes" baseAuthorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulistana">
<emphasis box="[1232,1398,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. paulistana</emphasis>
(Lopes, 1982)
</taxonomicName>
by having a vesica with a rounded lobe in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1164,1772,1798]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Figs 6D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1180,1220,1772,1798]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">7D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes H. S." box="[1236,1395,1772,1798]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" pagination="285 - 294" refId="ref11227" refString="Lopes H. S. 1982 a. Notes on American Sarcophagidae (Diptera) with descriptions of seven new species. Revista Brasileira de Biologia 42: 285 - 294." type="journal article" year="1982">Lopes 1982a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 58). 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[289,565,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[289,565,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Dexosarcophaga limon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[573,664,1807,1833]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[720,819,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[720,819,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[827,917,1807,1833]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lopes" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[1237,1398,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulistana">
<emphasis box="[1237,1398,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. paulistana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the distally completely rounded vesica (
<figureCitation box="[710,811,1842,1868]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Figs 6D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[826,864,1842,1868]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">7D</figureCitation>
) and with a digitiform projection distally in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lopes" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[189,353,1877,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulistana">
<emphasis box="[189,353,1877,1903]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. paulistana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes H. S." box="[371,530,1877,1903]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" pagination="285 - 294" refId="ref11227" refString="Lopes H. S. 1982 a. Notes on American Sarcophagidae (Diptera) with descriptions of seven new species. Revista Brasileira de Biologia 42: 285 - 294." type="journal article" year="1982">Lopes 1982a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 58). Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[763,868,1877,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[763,868,1877,1903]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. limon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[879,972,1878,1904]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be differentiated from those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[191,288,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[191,288,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[294,384,1913,1939]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the following features: ST5 with arm-like processes almost parallel-sides in middle part, apically rounded, and almost half as long as sternite (
<figureCitation box="[861,953,1948,1974]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
), cercus almost straight in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[196,289,1983,2009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
), and juxta with small spines apically (
<figureCitation box="[753,882,1983,2009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[240,1343,278,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-11@13.[232,1355,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Dexosarcophaga limon sp. nov., ♂, holotype (INBio [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823744" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823744/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">Fig. 6D–E</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[937,1036,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[937,1036,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="121">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1044,1138,1983,2009]" pageId="12" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, these features appear as follows: ST5 with arm-like processes gradually tapering, apically pointed and distinctly shorter than half of sternite, and with two small but distinct lobes projecting near the midline (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1226,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); apical half of cercus curved anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[487,579,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
), and juxta with small spines only at base (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1212,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
